Oct 30 2009 	Stylish santuary in the city that never sleeps!	We arrived approaching midnight on a stormy October evening after a nightmarish flight with BA (don't ask!). Immediately as you enter the tasteful lobby area you are greeted with an air of warmth, courtesy and professionalism from the exceptional staff. The room was perfect for us - young(ish!) professional couple: smart decor, if lacking attention to detail on the finishing in places (but still incredible value for the price); beautifully soft linen and bedding for you to collapse into at the end of another hectic NYC day; large flatscreen TV with great selection of channels (in comparison with European hotels); desk/dressing table area with a genorous helping of electrical sockets for all your technilogical gizmos; full-length well-lit mirror to check that you look vaguely presentable; window-ledge cushioned seating area allowing you to admire the views whilst planning your itenary for the day. The only slight letdown for us was the bathroom, which could've used a little TLC: the bathtub was quite worn with chipped enamel in places, plus it was very slow to drain so if you like long, lingering hot showers after a long days' sight-seeing you need to keep an eye on the water level in the tub; ours was close to overflowing on a few occassions! These, however, are very minor gripes especially when you consider the astonishing value for money this hotel offers. Included in the price was a delicious continental breakfast, comprising of bagels, cream cheese, croissants, jam, fresh fruit, yoghurt, muffins, fresh juice and tea/coffee. Another major plus-point is the location, right in the heart of bustling Manhattan, a few blocks from the Empire State Building and a little further to Times Square. You're also a stone's throw from the magnificent Grand Central station from which you can access any part of the city (and beyond!) that your heart desires. We found the fourth floor 'Living Room' to be a marvellous asset too, especially to use the internet facilities to check in for our return flight and in that sometimes uncomfortable gulf between room check-out and the airport transfer. The thing that really set this place apart, though, was the amazing staff: helpful, friendly and full of great ideas and recommendations, these people really know their stuff - don't hesitate to ask them anything and everything about your stay in NYC! I would thoroughly recommend Morgans to anyone - I just hope your stay is as wonderful as ours was.	
