n to know what we planned for the day and how our day was on our return. On top of this my fiance had a slight medical emergency very early in the morning of one of our stays - I had to call the front desk who suggested a local hospital that provided 24 hour care. The staff member at the time helped me get a cab and ensured the driver knew exactly where to take us. Hours late after we arrived the same staff member was very helpful in wanting to know if everything was okay, and offered further assistance and was incredibly courteous. Overall the staff are the best I have come accross in a hotel (both international and domestic) - and when I next travel to New York the easiest decision I will make is staying once again at Morgan's.My only tiny negative would be the fact that there was not a free Wi-Fi service for guests - but this is not something that you come accross often at hotels, so I wouldn't even call this a complaint - just something that would make Morgan's even more superior than they already are.Overall - easily the best hotel stay I have had - I would recommend them to any other traveller I knew going to New York and I will stay there on my next jaunt to New York City. Thanks again Morgan's.	
